      <head>Dr. Rüdinger</head>
      <div>
        <p>Writer on music, who wrote for, among other periodicals, <title level="j">Der Merker</title>. </p>
        
        <p>In July 1918, he contributed to <title level="j">Der Merker</title> a long obituary of <ref cRef="gartner_eduard">Eduard Gärtner</ref>. On
          July 17, 1919, Hans Gärtner approached Schenker to procure for Rüdinger a spoken or
          written recommendation to <ref cRef="breisach_paul">Paul Breisach</ref>, who was, in his turn, to act as an
          intermediary to Richard Strauss. </p>
      </div>
